Senator Abiodun Olujimi’s quest to retain her seat in the Red Chamber got a boost as women Stakeholders in the People’s Democratic Party(PDP) promised to work for her victory in the 2023 General Elections. This was the resolution at the end of the meeting convened by the  PDP Women Leader for Ekiti South Senatorial District, Mrs Arike Koledowo. The meeting was attended by the party’s women leaders in the six Local Governments areas in the Senatorial District, 64 Ward Leaders as well as the PDP’s State Women Leader, Hon. Sade Akinrinmola. The participants described the return ticket given to the two-term Senator as an acknowledgement of her quality and robust representation in the National Assembly. They promised to commence grassroots mobilisation for the PDP Senatorial candidate. In her remarks, Olujimi thanked the PDP women for the show of love promising to intensify efforts at giving them a voice in the party and at the National Assembly. Senator Olujimi enjoined them to remain committed to the party ideology while assuring them of improvement in dispensing dividends of democracy at the grassroots.